'''Bashir Rage Shiiraar''' (born 1965) is a [[Somalia|Somali]] secular rebel leader and [[businessman]] who hails from the [[Warsangali]] clan (an [[Abgaal]] subclan).<ref>[http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/library/news/2006/03/mil-060322-irin04.htm]</ref>
He became a member of the [[United States|US]]-backed [[Alliance for the Restoration of Peace and Counter-Terrorism]].
He was the head of the export department of the El-Ma An port which served as [[Mogadishu]]'s port following the closure of the city's main harbour in 1995.<ref>[http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?click_id=87&art_id=qw1085926140206B254&set_id=1]</ref>
