{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}} {{refimprove|date=October 2017}} {{Infobox settlement | name = CBD Belapur | native_name = | native_name_lang = | other_name = | settlement_type = Business District | image_skyline = Navi mumbai.jpg | image_caption = | map_caption = | pushpin_map = Mumbai | pushpin_label_position = left | coordinates = {{coord|19|1|1|N|73|2|22|E|display=inline,title}} | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{flag|India}} | subdivision_type1 = [[States and territories of India|State]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Maharashtra]] | subdivision_type2 = [[List of districts of India|District]] | subdivision_name2 = [[Thane]] | established_title = <!-- Established --> | established_date = | governing_body = CIDCO | unit_pref = Metric | area_total_km2 = | elevation_footnotes = | elevation_m = | population_footnotes = | population_total = | population_as_of = | population_density_km2 = auto | area_code_type = Telephone code | area_code = 022 | registration_plate = MH-43 | blank2_name_sec1 = Civic agency | blank2_info_sec1 = CIDCO | website = }}
[[File:CBD Belapur exit sign on Sion Panvel Highway.jpeg|300 px|thumbnail|Exit sign for CBD Belapur on [[Sion Panvel Highway]]]]
The '''Central Business District of Belapur''' (C.B.D Belapur) is a node of [[Navi Mumbai]]. The [[Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation]] is headquartered in Belapur. The Reserve Bank of India maintains a branch office at CBD Belapur. This area is one of the fastest developing region in Navi Mumbai in terms of new residential and commercial construction projects.{{fact|date=April 2017}} CBD Belapur is connected to other parts of Mumbai through railways, BEST & NMMT buses. It had a [[Water transport in Mumbai|ferry service]] for traveling to Elephanta caves from Sector-11.
CBD Belapur is a chief business district of Mumbai after Vashi, Bandra-Kurla Complex, Nariman Point and Worli.
CBD Belapur has been growing since the 1990s,{{fact|date=April 2017}} and is now home to colleges as well as a number of technology businesses.
==History== [[File:Belapur creek.jpg|thumb|100px|A view of Belapur Creek]] The area near Belapur was under [[Portuguese Empire|Portuguese]] rule around 1560, before it was captured by the [[Siddis]] of [[Janjira State|Janjira]]. In those days, the town was called Belawal by the locals, and Sambayo or Shabaz by the Portuguese. In 1682, the Portuguese recaptured Shabaz, only to lose it to the [[Maratha Empire|Marathas]] in 1733. In 1817, the [[British East India Company]] captured the area from the Marathas. It is the southernmost town in the [[Thane district]] as well as the Thane taluka.
==Economy== CBD Belapur houses several economic and government administrative and private companies' offices (including government offices and banks). Konkan Bhavan building houses several state government offices, like the Director of Town Planning and Public Works Department. The CGO Complex (Central Government Office) has offices of Chief Commissioner of Central Exice, Special Crime Branch, MTNL and Court. Other government offices include Cotton Corporation of India Ltd and the headquarters of Konkan Railway.
The Reserve Bank of India, State Bank of India (SBI), Bank of India, Punjab National Bank, Industrial Development Bank of India Limited (IDBI) and other nationalised banks have their presence here.
CBD Belapur is home to several call centres, including ChoiceConnex, Wipro BPO, Kaizen and SilkRoot. ChoiceConnex specialises in out-bound sales for US, Australia and UAE and has started domestic operations as well.{{fact|date=April 2017}} It has markets for local population in sectors 3, 4, 5 & 6. It has M.G.M. Hospital which covers the local population's medical needs.{{fact|date=April 2017}} A new charitable hospital, Acharyashri Nanesh Hospital, is scheduled to open{{when|date=April 2017}} in the artist village within Belapur. It has a number of restaurants and recreational grounds such as Sunil Gavaskar Maidan. International Technology Centre at the CBD Belapur railway station complex was built by CIDCO as an Infotech hub.
==Administrative offices== CBD Belapur is also important as regards to administrative purpose as many central, state and local government offices are situated here: [[File:Kokan Bhavan.jpg|thumb|Konkan Bhavan]] * '''Konkan Bhavan (State)''' * '''CGO (Central Government Offices Complex)''' * '''NMMC (Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation)''' * '''CIDCO Bhavan ( Head office of Navi Mumbai City and Industrial Dev. Company)
==Transport== CBD belapur is connecting soon by the new international airport which is navi mumbai international airport(NMIA) .which is in construction in belapur west side near to the nmmc headquarters. CBD Belapur is accessible from other parts of [[Navi Mumbai]] and from [[Mumbai]] by road and rail transport facilities. [[Belapur railway station]] lies on the harbour line and [[Sion Panvel Highway]] passes through this node. [[Palm Beach Marg]] connects CBD Belapur directly with Vashi. Railway service is up to Panvel. [[File:Belapur Rly Stn.jpg|thumb|Belapur Railway Station]] [[File:BEST-NMMT-buses-CBD-Belapur-Rains.jpg|Buses at the CBD Belapur bus station|thumb]]
BEST buses are available from CBD Belapur to Vashi, Chembur, Sion, Dadar, Bandra and Ghatkopar. NMMT buses are available from CBD Belapur to Vashi, Thane, Dombivali, Kalyan, Badlapur, Uran, Taloja and Panvel. NMMT AC Volvo buses are available from CBD Belapur to Vashi, Panvel, Chembur, Sion, Dadar, Bandra and Borivali. Auto rickshaws is the primary mode of transport within the node owing the small area occupied by the node.{{fact|date=April 2017}}
