[[File:Kunstmesse München No58 Main Entrance 02.jpg|{{largethumb}}|Main entrance of ''{{lang|de|Kunstmesse München}} 58'' in 2013]] The '''{{lang|de|Kunstmesse München}}''' (''[[Munich]] Art Fair'') is the oldest art and antiques fair in [[Germany]]. Held annually in the autumn with a run-time of ten days, it is a fair for the general public, attended by leading national and international exhibitors. For some time now its venue is the historic {{lang|de|Postpalast}} in Munich, on Wredestraße near the [[Hackerbrücke]]. The offer ranges from [[Protohistory]] and Ancient History (such as [[Art of ancient Egypt|Egypt]]) via the [[arts and crafts]] of the [[Middle Ages]] and the [[Renaissance]] through to [[Modern art|art and design of Modernism]] until approximately 1970, with occasional exceptions. The fair is organised by ''Expo Management Kiel'', its conceptual sponsor is, in continuation of the {{lang|de|[[Bundesverband Deutscher Galerien und Kunsthändler|Deutscher Kunsthandelsverband]]}}, the newly founded {{lang|de|Kunsthändlerverband Deutschland}} (a [[Eingetragener Verein|registered association]]).<ref>Annegret Erhard: [http://www.nzz.ch/feuilleton/kunsthandel-auktionen/die-traditionelle-kunstmesse-muenchen-im-eleganten-postpalast-1.18169790 ''Die traditionelle Kunstmesse München im eleganten Postpalast.''] [[Neue Zürcher Zeitung|NZZ]], 18 October 2013</ref>
== History == The {{lang|de|Kunstmesse München}} set out in 1956 as {{lang|de|Deutsche Kunst und Antiquitätenmesse}} under the conceptual sponsorship of the {{lang|de|Deutscher Kunsthandelsverband}}. Until 1988, the leading event of its kind, it took place in the {{lang|de|[[Haus der Kunst]]}} in Munich. Thereafter it was, for reasons of space, relocated to the {{lang|de|Messe München}} (Munich Trade Fair), finally in the [[Neue Messe München|fairground at Riem]].<ref>Brita Sachs: [http://www.faz.net/aktuell/feuilleton/kunstmarkt/messen/kunstmesse-muenchen-mit-leichter-hand-ein-museales-ambiente-schaffen-1490461.html ''Kunstmesse München, Mit leichter Hand ein museales Ambiente schaffen.''] [[Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung]], 13 October 2007.</ref> After a re-organization (and a transitory name change to ''Fine Art & Antiques'' for legal reasons), the historic {{lang|de|Postpalast}} in Munich was determined as the venue.<ref>[http://www.ilgiornaledellarte.com/articoli/2011/10/110638.html ''"Oktoberfest". Spumeggiante Baviera. A Monaco si gioca un derby: "Kunstmesse" contro "Highlights"''], Il Giornale dell'arte, 313, October 2011; Annette Lettau: [http://www.zeit.de/2012/42/Kunstmesse-Muenchen-Altmeister-Fayencen ''Amüsanter Augentrug, Gleich drei Kunstmessen locken nach München.''] [[Die Zeit]], 18 December 2012; and Brita Sachs: [http://www.faz.net/aktuell/feuilleton/kunstmarkt/muenchner-kunstwoche-kleine-und-grosse-wunderwerke-13253919.html ''Kleine und große Wunderwerke.''] [[Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung]], 8 November 2014</ref>
== Offer == The offer comprises all periods and basically all genres of arts and crafts are on show, although the focus may vary. Objects from art and [[Cabinet of curiosities|curiosity cabinets]] and [[textile art]] (rugs and carpets) are included, so are [[Antique car|vintage cars]].<ref>Bettina Beckert: [https://www.handelsblatt.com/panorama/kultur-kunstmarkt/kunst-messe-muenchen-aufmarsch-der-antiquitaetenhaendler/3563842-all.html ''Aufmarsch der Antiquitätenhändler.''] [[Handelsblatt]], 15 October 2010; Eva Komarek: [http://online.wirtschaftsblatt.at/investor/investor_05102012.pdf ''Kunstgenuss in München – von Altägypten bis zur Moderne.''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310003322/http://online.wirtschaftsblatt.at/investor/investor_05102012.pdf |date=2016-03-10 }} Wirtschaftsblatt Investor (Wien), No 76, 5 October 2012, pp. 16–17; [[Gerhard Charles Rump]]: [https://www.welt.de/print-welt/article487769/Kunst-fuer-140-Mio-auf-einem-Stand.html ''Kunst für 140 Mio. auf einem Stand. Auf der 46. Kunst Messe München kann man sogar Paganinis Notenpult kaufen.''] [[Die Welt]], 17 November 2001.</ref> {{wide image|Kunstmesse München No58 Panoramic View 01.jpeg|1024px|Panoramic view of ''Kunstmesse München 58'' in Munich's Postpalast 2013}}
